Name: Sploosh-o-matic
Card Description: Sploosh is my old main! Thank you Sploosh!!

Name: Splattershot Jr.
Card Description: Drawing Jrs - like playing them - is my comfort zone, but this time I wanted to celebrate the Jr's expanded ink tank! Sure, it's the Splatoon 2 design but we found that many of the cards feature equipment from the previous game. Perhaps the in-universe Tableturf cards were developed in Inkopolis during Splatoon 2, in time to be popular for the start of Splatoon 3.

Name: Splash-o-matic
Card Description: Splash-o-matic is a versatile card. Use this card to close off any entrances from your opponent. Make sure to put the special tile near corners.

Name: Aerospray MG
Card Description: The original Aerospray MG card had a very nervous looking Octoling featured on it and I thought it was too cute not to recreate. Someone needs Ink Resistance Up!

Name: Splattershot Pro
Card Description: I just loved this guy's silly manatee sweatshirt :D

Name: .96 Gal
Card Description: I was really excited to work on the 96. Gal, I knew from the start I wanted my drawings to have a bit more of a pop for this project so I wanted to mess around with perspective to create a more dynamic composition. It was a fairly hard challenge for me but I'm super happy with the result of this one!

Name: Jet Squelcher
Card Description: edgelord

Name: Luna Blaster
Card Description: I was once taunted by a Luna Blaster after they dropped down on me with their zipcaster. I still think about it till this day because honestly it was a good play to get rid of me from my position as a charger.

Name: Rapid Blaster
Card Description: I like the original Rapid Blasters pose a lot so I wanted to keep it but make it a tad more dynamic than just standing there. I changed the hat from the card's since I couldn't find decipher which it was to the howdy hat for a more 'cowboy' look.

Name: L-3 Nozzlenose
Card Description: The hardest thing was making sure the L-3 looked in proportion. It's really interesting to translate something so stylized like Splatoon into my own style

Name: Squeezer
Card Description: memelord

Name: Inkbrush
Card Description: As an Inkbrush main myself, I wanted to encapsulate the "swing and hope for the best" style of playing I tend to have haha.

Name: Splatterscope
Card Description: While the splatterscope isn't a weapon I'm exactly skilled with, I really wanted to convey the drama and prowess that I feel sniper mains often have. I hope the dramatic lighting and forced perspective in this card helps to show that! :}

Name: Explosher
Card Description: Explosher fans rise up!! It's my go-to main weapon of choice in almost every mode. I decided to depart from my usual style and just let loose with the redraw, and it ended up paying off with a super stylized grafitti-esque card. I had just as much fun drawing this as I do playing Explosher!!

Name: Heavy Splatling
Card Description: The original card was based on a Splatling win pose in the first Splatoon game, so of course I had to recreate it!

Name: Hydra Splatling
Card Description: I wanted to capture the power and weight behind the Hydra Splatling, and how it feels to use it! Splatlings are my favourite class, so I had lots of fun working on this piece!

Name: Dapple Dualies
Card Description: For the dapples since they are one of my mains I tried to think about how I play them really fast and it reminded me of Sonic so I thought it'd be fun to mimic his iconic pose from Adventure 1. Since both of my cards hard yellow ink I applied a gradient map to make the ink more greenish in color to make it pop a bit more.

Name: Dark Tetra Dualies
Card Description: The true quick respawn runners, you will always see them equip the ability so if they get splatted they’ll be back in a blink of an eye to try and get you again. Deadliest of the Dualies next to the Splat Dualies.

Name: Tenta Brella
Card Description: The Tenta Brella was a challenge due to its shape and size! It was a lot of fun playing with perspective in this piece

Name: Undercover Brella
Card Description: The Undercover is one of my favorite weapons, and the only brella I like; too bad it's widely considered the worst brella in the game. Justice for the Undercover! I also just really like this Inkling design in general. Done in FireAlpaca.

Name: Tri-Stringer
Card Description:
Push the boundaries on the tableturf board, the turf field, and in art!!! 
The tristringer card is already iconic and has the perfect posing, so I didn't want to change it too much. However, an in-your-face perspective and some fun lighting felt like the flair it deserved!! 
Shoot high and aim far!!

Name: REEF-LUX 450
Card Description: This card was super fun to work on !! I chose the Reef-Lux 450 as I thought it would be a good weapon to do a dynamic pose with, and it came out really well !! I'm not the greatest at Tableturf, but imo it's one of the best new features in Splatoon 3 and I love collecting all the cards !!

Name: Splat Bomb
Card Description: The pose is inspired by the original splat bomb sprite from Splatoon 2! Although, I decided to insert one of my Splatoon OCs, Bcap (╹▽╹)>

Name: Sprinkler
Card Description: Sprinkler is love, sprinkler is life. We need a burst bomb special but with sprinklers. There can never be enough.

Name: Splash Wall
Card Description: Ironically enough, I don't use splash wall very often. I tend to main Aerospray RG and Dynamo Roller. I do like the design/use of the sub though, and one of my friends always jokes about being a menace with it. So I really tried to capture the energy she has when playing! xD

Name: Fizzy Bomb
Card Description: I was in the opposite position for the fizzy bomb, I wanted it to look dynamic, sure, but it was  somewhat hard to envision an extreme pose with a can grenade. I was debating on making it look like it was about to burst but I felt it wouldn't be as recognizable, so I then tried to make it look as if it was bouncing against the card. Like the gal, I'm super happy with the end result!

Name: Ink Mine
Card Description: I immediately fell in love with the tableturf style as soon as it was first shown in the pre-launch trailers, even drew my own card in the style like many others did! Both cards I submit feature my own octo you might have seen around in turf war, and I hope capture the essence of my playstyle. Hope to see you at the newly installed online tableturf battle tables in Splatsville someday!!!

Name: Toxic Mist
Card Description: I love being a squidkid and had a blast working on this project! Woomy!!

Name: Triple Inkstrike
Card Description: The Inkstrike returns as a pencil case!? Pencil sharpeners are homing beacons for the missiles...somehow.

Name: Sheldon
Card Description: Sheldon's the absolute best boy in all of Splatoon! I just HAD to go all in with this one to try and do him due dilligence. I think I did a pretty good job, too! The shell perspective was SO HARD though. Done in Clip Studio Paint.

Name: Harmony
Card Description: Harmony jamming late at night, too absorbed in her work to move somewhere brighter as her bioluminescence provides a dim glow.

Name: Murch
Card Description: It's best to pair Murch with the Wave Breaker, these cards make a large wall to prevent the opponent from invading your turf. Best in straight and narrow paths like Main Street, Lakefront Property and River Drift. Plus, you have 24 spaces covered with just these two cards!

Name: Captain
Card Description: As someone who's been a fan since Splatoon 1, being able to illustrate Captain Agent 3 for the Arty Siege deck was an honor. I just had to make Captain to look as cool as they act in game!

Name: Callie
Card Description: I wanted to draw Callie in the pointing pose she does in story mode!! It left a big impression on me when I saw the New Squidbeak group do it all together!!

Name: Judd
Card Description: cute little kitty!!

Name: Toni Kensa
Card Description: Even in the third iteration of the game, Toni Kensa remains one of my favourite brands, not only because of its stylishness, but also because of the mystery surrounding its namesake. I hope we get to see more of this clean-cut, powerful and yet elusive brand as Splatoon 3 ages!

Name: Emberz
Card Description: The day I finished drawing this card I finally got the 30+ Emberz star badge so I think it was meant to be <3

Name: Octodisco
Card Description: Thanks to this guy Octarians are stayin' alive.

Name: Slammin' Lid
Card Description: Slammin' Lids are my favorite Boss Salmonids. They're so goofy! Because of their verticality, I took this as an opportunity to draw them in a tall perspective.

Name: Griller
Card Description:
the griller is hands down my favorite salmonid and i love it to bits. it just wants to give you a hug!!
i enjoyed refining my lineless style for this piece so much that i rendered most of my other card the same way :]

Name: Tower Control
Card Description: Take a step back from fighting and listen to the tower’s tune. It changes depending on which team you are on.

Name: Tentatek Splattershot
Card Description: i'm an avid tableturf player—this project gives me so much life and i'm elated to contribute to it! although i'm not familiar with this weapon's style of play, the character's body language spoke to me... i really wanted to mimic those adrenaline-rush vibes

Name: Big Swig Roller
Card Description: schluuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuurp

Name: The Eel Deal - Frye
Card Description: I was SUPER excited to get to draw Frye since she's my fave of the Deep Cut trio! (Gotta love a bestie who adds too much chocolate/sugar to her coffees, I say sipping on my own coffee monstrosity rn) Initially, this art was for the regular Frye card, but Apollo and his gift of prophecy made a story mode Frye card to have in game, so we moved it over here. I'm really proud with how she came out! :D

Name: The Hype Manta Storm - Big Man
